{"article_id":"cfdl9fKbuea5RTVU","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Washington ( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The Senate confirmed Brett Kavanaugh , 53 , to the Supreme Court on Saturday ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"where he could easily serve for more than two decades","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and change how the nation 's laws are interpreted .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"He replaces centrist conservative Justice Anthony Kennedy ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"who retired this summer .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Here 's where Kavanaugh ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"who was a judge on the US Court of Appeals for the DC Circuit for 12 years ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"stands on some hot-button issues :","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"During his first round of testimony before the Senate Judiciary Committee , Kavanaugh said","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"he views Roe v. Wade , the landmark ruling","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that legalized abortion nationwide ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"as `` important precedent of the Supreme Court ''","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that has been `` reaffirmed many times . ''","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Yet he declined to say","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"he would not vote to reverse Roe ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that such a vow","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"-- on any case --","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"would violate judicial norms .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"He also defended a dissenting opinion","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"he wrote last year","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"when the full DC Circuit allowed a 17-year-old to end her pregnancy over objections from the Trump administration .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"In his dissent , Kavanaugh wrote","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"the Supreme Court has held","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that `` the government has permissible interests","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"in favoring fetal life ,","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"protecting the best interests of a minor ,","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"and refraining from facilitating abortion . ''","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"He wrote","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that the high court has `` held","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that the government may further those interests","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"so long as it does not impose an undue burden on a woman","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"seeking an abortion . ''","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"the majority opinion was `` based on a constitutional principle as novel","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"as it is wrong :","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"a new right for unlawful immigrant minors in US government detention","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"to obtain immediate abortion on demand . ''","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"2006 :","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Kavanaugh discusses Roe v. Wade","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"MUST WATCH 2006 :","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Kavanaugh discusses Roe v. Wade","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"00:50","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"Overall , his testimony reinforced his past writings","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"suggesting","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"he would permit the government to more strictly regulate abortion , for example , with additional requirements","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"that could delay the procedure","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"or stiffer rules for physicians","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"who would perform it .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Trump has long vowed to appoint justices","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"who would reverse Roe","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"and allow the states to determine","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"whether abortion should be legal .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Kennedy had been a swing vote in favor of abortion rights .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"During his confirmation hearings , Kavanaugh declined to elaborate on his views on executive power or protections for a president","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"who might face an investigation and subpoena .","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"When Democratic Sen. Dianne Feinstein of California asked Kavanaugh","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"if a sitting president could be compelled to respond to a subpoena ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"he declined to offer his views .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"`` I ca n't give you an answer on that hypothetical question , ''","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"In a 2009 Minnesota Law Review article , Kavanaugh had written","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"that `` Congress might consider a law","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"exempting a President","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"-- while in office --","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"from criminal prosecution and investigation ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"including from questioning by criminal prosecutors or defense counsel . ''","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"In the same article , however , he noted ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"`` If the President does something dastardly ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"the impeachment process is available . ''","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Kavanaugh has demonstrated a tendency toward suspicion of , rather than deference to , regulatory agency interpretations of federal laws .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"`` It 's all about the statute","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"you write , ''","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"he emphasized to Sen. Amy Klobuchar , a Minnesota Democrat ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"noting","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"he would not impose new requirements","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"-- on businesses , for example --","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"that Congress had not made explicit .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"That view ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"as Klobuchar noted ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"can limit regulatory safeguards on the job , environmental rules and consumer protection .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Kavanaugh 's views on government regulation may be best exemplified by his dissent in the case of a killer whale","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"that attacked a SeaWorld trainer .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"As Kavanaugh criticized a Labor Department move","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"to sanction SeaWorld","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"following the drowning of a trainer by the orca Tilikum ,","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"he declared","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"that the agency had `` stormed headlong into a new regulatory arena ''","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"and warned","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"that regulators would try to impose new safety requirements on sports , the circus and more .","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"Overall , his view is that agencies should exercise authority","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"as clearly spelled out in federal statutes","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"and that judges should not ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"as occurred in the SeaWorld case ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"defer to agency interpretations","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"that go beyond what 's explicit in a law .","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"In opinions and speeches , Kavanaugh has questioned a ruling in a 1984 Supreme Court case , Chevron v. Natural Resources Defense Council ,","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"that said","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"judges should defer to agency interpretations of ambiguous laws .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"That ,","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"he said in a 2017 speech ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"`` encourages agency aggressiveness on a large scale . ''","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"Kavanaugh said generally during his hearings","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"that `` it 's important to recognize","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"that the First Amendment to the Constitution , as well as many statutes , of course , protect religious liberty in the United States ...","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"and","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"as I 've said in some of my opinions ,","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"we are all equally American","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"no matter what religion we are or no religion at all --","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"and that means","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"religious speakers and religious people have a right to their place in the public square . ''","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"On the DC Circuit , Kavanaugh dissented in the 2015 case of Priests for Life v. Department of Health and Human Services ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"focused on a religious exemption to the Affordable Care Act .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"He dissented","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"when the DC Circuit declined a full court review of a religious group 's objection to the process for employers","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"seeking to opt out of the mandate","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"to provide insurance coverage for contraceptives .","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"Priests for Life had challenged the process","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"for certifying eligibility for exemptions ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"contending","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"the paperwork involved burdened religious rights .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"Kavanaugh agreed ,","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"saying ,","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"`` To plaintiffs , the act","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"of submitting this form","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"would , in their religious judgment , impermissibly facilitate delivery of contraceptive and abortifacient coverage . ''","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"that rather than a form , the group could","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"-- as the Supreme Court had allowed in separate cases --","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"be permitted to simply notify the secretary of health and human services in writing","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"that it objects to providing coverage for contraceptives .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"In 2011 , Kavanaugh dissented from a majority opinion of the DC Circuit","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"that upheld a ban","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"that applied to semiautomatic rifles in the District of Columbia .","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"In his dissent , he wrote","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"that the Supreme Court had previously `` held","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"that handguns","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"-- the vast majority of which today are semiautomatic --","depth":15},{"id":141,"text":"are constitutionally protected","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"because they have not traditionally been banned","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"and are in common use by law-abiding citizens . ''","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"Citing a previous high court ruling ,","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"Kavanaugh went on to say ,","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"`` It follows from Heller 's protection of semiautomatic handguns that semiautomatic rifles are also constitutionally protected","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"and that DC 's ban on them is unconstitutional . ''","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"Feinstein pressed Kavanaugh on his dissent during his confirmation hearings ,","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"asking ,","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"`` What did you base your conclusion on","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"that assault weapons are in common use ? '' `","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"` I had to follow precedent , ''","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"Kavanaugh said ,","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"adding","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"that `` semiautomatic rifles are widely possessed in the United States ...","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"so that seemed to fit common use","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"in not being a dangerous and unusual weapon .","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"That was the basis of my dissent . ''","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"In 2015 , Kavanaugh wrote an opinion","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"defending the US government 's controversial metadata collection program ,","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"in part citing national security considerations .","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"He wrote","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"that the program `` is entirely consistent with the Fourth Amendment , ''","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"which protects against unreasonable search and seizure .","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"He wrote","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"that the program `` does not capture the content of communications , but rather the time and duration of calls and the numbers","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"called , ''","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"and said","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"it `` serves a critically important special need","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"-- preventing terrorist attacks on the United States . ''","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"Kavanaugh argued","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"`` that critical national security need outweighs the impact on privacy","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"occasioned by this program . ''","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"In a 2017 dissent , Kavanaugh said","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"he believed","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"that Obama-era net neutrality regulations were `` unlawful ''","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"and wrote","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"that the policy violated the First Amendment .","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"At issue were rules","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"approved by the Federal Communications Commission in 2015","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"to more strictly regulate the Internet .","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"The rules ,","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"based on the principle of `` net neutrality , ''","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"were intended to provide equal opportunity for Internet speeds and access to websites .","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"In a May 2017 order , a majority of the DC Circuit declined to review an earlier decision","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"siding with the FCC .","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"Under the Trump administration , the FCC has since moved to dismantle the regulation .","depth":12},{"id":188,"text":"Kavanaugh wrote in his 2017 dissenting opinion","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"that the regulation was consequential","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"and `` transforms the Internet . ''","depth":14},{"id":191,"text":"But he said","depth":15},{"id":192,"text":"the rule `` impermissibly infringes on the Internet service providers ' editorial discretion , ''","depth":15},{"id":193,"text":"and he suggested","depth":15},{"id":194,"text":"the FCC had overreached","depth":16},{"id":195,"text":"in issuing the regulation .","depth":16},{"id":196,"text":"`` Congress did not clearly authorize the FCC to issue the net neutrality rule , ''","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"he wrote .","depth":14}],"relations":[{"parent":395,"left":0,"right":394,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":394,"left":235,"right":393,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":235,"left":202,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":200,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":1,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":201,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":204,"right":233,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":204,"left":203,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":214,"right":232,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":214,"left":208,"right":213,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":208,"left":9,"right":207,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":207,"left":205,"right":206,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":205,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":12,"right":13,"re